# SYSTEM STATE DEFINITION (V1.0)
**"The Blackboard Architecture"**

## 1. The Core Principle
> **"No Agent Speaks. All Agents Write."**

In AXON, Agents ([Orion](file:///C:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/scratch/AXON-boilerplate/src/components/dashboard/OrionStudio.tsx#5-300), [Calliope](file:///C:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/scratch/AXON-boilerplate/src/types/agent_types.ts#50-57), `Echo`) are **strictly decoupled**.
They do NOT call each other's functions.
They do NOT pass variables directly.

Instead, they interact with the **Global System Context** (The Blackboard).

